'''Appurv Gupta''' is an [[India|Indian]] [[Stand-up comedy|stand up comedian]], [[Hinglish]] [[stand-up comedian]] and a [[satirist]] from India.<ref name="ibn">{{cite web|title=20 Indian stand-up comedians to watch out for in 2014|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/20-indian-standup-comedians-to-watch-out-for-in-2014/445086-79.html|accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref><ref name=metro/><ref>{{cite web|title=Professionals make a laughing matter of their jobs|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/relationships/work/Professionals-make-a-laughing-matter-of-their-jobs/articleshow/22114264.cms|accessdate=28 August 2014}}</ref>

Gupta is a graduate of [[Jaypee Institute of Information Technology]], Noida in [[Bachelor of Technology]]. He completed his engineering in 2012 and chose to be a stand-up comedian rather than working for corporate offices.<ref name=metro>{{cite web|title=It's a fun-filled show time!|url=http://epaper.metroindia.com/story.aspx?id=4813&boxid=98332216&ed_date=2014-5-29&ed_code=820009&ed_page=13#.U4bfFCp3AfY.gmail|accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref> He has done around 1000 shows since then, including corporate performances for [[Bharti Airtel|Airtel]], [[Tanishq]], [[Adobe Systems|Adobe]], [[American Express|Amex]] and [[Radio Mirchi]].<ref name=deccan>{{cite web|title=City boy tickles the Capital's funny bone with clean humour|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/381690/city-boy-tickles-capital039s-funny.html|accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref> His most applauded act is ''Appurview - Laugh with an Engineer'' which describes life from the point-of-view of an engineer.<ref name=toi>{{cite web|title=Techie-turned-comic shuns stage cliches|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/gurgaon/Techie-turned-comic-shuns-stage-cliches/articleshow/32515801.cms|accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=There is no vulgarity in my shows: Appurv Gupta|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/theatre/There-is-no-vulgarity-in-my-shows-Appurv-Gupta/articleshow/33182128.cms|accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Engineering humour not designs|url=http://millenniumpost.in/NewsContent.aspx?NID=54716|accessdate=28 August 2014}}</ref>

Gupta was ranked second in "Top 20 Indian stand-up comedian in 2014" by [[CNN-IBN]],<ref name="ibn"/> and was shortlisted in the [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Forbes India 100 Celebrity]] nominees list of 2015 by [[Forbes India]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Forbes India Celebrity 100 Nominees List for 2015|url=http://forbesindia.com/article/special/forbes-india-celebrity-100-nominees-list-for-2015/41475/1|accessdate=17 December 2015|work=Forbes India|date=4 November 2015}}</ref>

